//Anatomical variants


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 07 - Femoropatellar joint of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Anatomical variants' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Accessory ossification centers' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vertical position' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sulcus angle of the femoral trochlea' checkbox is enabled
And 'Trochlear dysplasia according to Dejour' checkbox is enabled
And 'TT-TG distance' checkbox is enabled
And 'Plica mediopatellaris' checkbox is enabled
And 'Plica lateralis patellae' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Accessory ossification centers' checkbox
Then 'Patella bipartita' radio button is enabled
And 'Patella tripartita' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Vertical position' checkbox
Then 'Visual selection' radio button is enabled
And 'Insall-Salvati-Index' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Visual selection' radio button
Then 'Patella alta' radio button is enabled
And 'Patella baja' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Insall-Salvati-Index' radio button
Then 'Largest vertical cc extension of the patella' input field is enabled
And 'Length of the patellar ligament' input field is enabled
And 'Insall-Salvati-Index' automatically calculated input field is enabled
And 'Patella alta' automatically calculated radio button is enabled
And 'No pathological finding' automatically calculated radio button is enabled
And 'Patella baja' automatically calculated radio button is enabled

When I select 'Sulcus angle of the femoral trochlea' checkbox
Then 'Value in degrees' input field is enabled
And '>145Â° = Trochlea Dysplasia' automatically calculated checkbox


When I select 'Trochlear dysplasia according to Dejour' checkbox
Then 'Type A: shallow trochlear groove' radio button is enabled
And 'Type B: flattened or convex trochlea' radio button is enabled
And 'Type C: trochlear facet asymmetry with too high lateral facet' radio button is enabled
And 'Type D: type B + C & a vertical link between facets' radio button is enabled


When I select 'TT-TG distance' checkbox
Then 'Distance' input field is enabled
And '< 15 mm: normal' automatically calculated radio button is enabled
And '15-20 mm: borderline' automatically calculated radio button is enabled
And '> 20 mm: Abnormal, thus indicating patellar instability' automatically calculated radio button is enabled


When I select 'Plica mediopatellaris' checkbox
Then 'Width' input field is enabled
And 'Precondylar extension' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chondropathy medial patellar facet' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chondropathy medial trochlear ridge' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Plica lateralis patellae' checkbox
Then 'Width' input field is enabled
And 'Precondylar extension Plica-assoc. cartilage findings' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chondropathy lateral patellar facet' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chondropathy lateral trochlear ridge' checkbox is enabled